main event: The witness observed a bright, self-luminous, and intensely white object that moved at a high speed, made abrupt turns and changes in speed, and appeared to be heading southwest. The object was observed for less than a minute.
interesting points: The object was quite bright and self-luminous, with an intense white color.
It made abrupt turns and changes in speed, appearing to be flying erratically.
The object was observed at a relatively high altitude, probably several thousand feet up.
It did not seem to leave any trail or exhaust behind it.
The witness, an engineer by profession, stated that the object was unlike any aircraft they had seen before and believed it to be a UFO.
sighted object: a bright, self-luminous, intensely white object
